                                                                              Diagnosis and optimization of application prefetching performance
                                                                              
            
                                                                                
               
                                                                              • Gabriel Marin, 
                                                                                • 
               
                                                                              • Collin McCurdy, 
                                                                                • 
               
                                                                              • Jeffrey S. Vetter
                                                                                • 
            
                                                                              
            
                                                                              ICS '13: Proceedings of the 27th international ACM conference on International conference on
                     supercomputingJune 2013, pp 303–312https://doi.org/10.1145/2464996.2465014
                                                                              
            
                                                                              
               		
               
                                                                              Hardware prefetchers are effective at recognizing streaming memory access patterns

                                                                                                                                                                              The Impact of Software Fault Prediction in Real-World Application: An Automated Approach for Software Engineering
                                                                                                                                                                              
            
                                                                                                                                                                                
               
                                                                                                                                                                              • Md. Razu Ahmed, 
                                                                                                                                                                                • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                              • Md. Asraf Ali, 
                                                                                                                                                                                • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                              • Nasim Ahmed,

                                                                                                                                                                              • Md. Fahad Bin Zamal,

                                                                                                                                                                                • 
            
                                                                                                                                                                              
            
                                                                                                                                                                              ICCDE 2020: Proceedings of 2020 the 6th International Conference on Computing and Data EngineeringJanuary 2020, pp 247–251https://doi.org/10.1145/3379247.3379278

                                                                                                                                                                                                                              PPoPP '09: Proceedings of the 14th ACM SIGPLAN symposium on Principles and practice of parallel
                     programmingFebruary 2009, pp 229–240https://doi.org/10.1145/1504176.1504210
                                                                                                                                                                                                                              
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                              
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                              Understanding why the performance of a multithreaded program does not improve linearly
                  with the number of cores in a shared-memory node populated with one or more multicore
                  processors is a problem of growing practical importance.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Model-based enhancement of software performance for precision critical systems

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  This paper describes how the application specific knowledge represented in ontologies
                  is used to improve the processing of user interventions in a multilingual dialogue

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Evaluating the WaterRpg software watermarking model on Java application programs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      • Ioannis Chionis, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      • Maria Chroni,

Nikolopoulos

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Recently, we have presented a dynamic watermarking model, which we named WaterRpg,
                  for embedding a reducible permutation graph F[π*] into an application program P. The main idea behind the proposed watermarking model is to modify the dynamic call-graph
                  ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        Modeling and analyzing performance of software for wireless sensor networks
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        • Luca Berardinelli, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        • Vittorio Cortellessa, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        • Stefano Pace
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          • 
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        SESENA '11: Proceedings of the 2nd Workshop on Software Engineering for Sensor Network ApplicationsMay 2011, pp 13–18https://doi.org/10.1145/1988051.1988055
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        The development of software for Wireless Sensor Networks (WSN) is mostly based on
                  code-and-fix techniques. Up today model-driven engineering techniques have only been
                  limitedly considered in this domain, although they would enable a set of activities
                  ...

Kleinsorge

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          Caches are notorious for their unpredictability. It is difficult or even impossible
                  to predict if a memory access will result in a definite cache hit or miss. This unpredictability
                  is highly undesired especially when designing real-time systems where ...

                  of long-running applications. This feature is however severely limited in current
                  virtual machines for object-oriented languages. In particular, changes to classes

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                Continuous software performance assessment: detecting performance problems of software
                     libraries on every build
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                • Christoph Laaber
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  • 
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                ISSTA 2019: Proceedings of the 28th ACM SIGSOFT International Symposium on Software Testing and
                     AnalysisJuly 2019, pp 410–414https://doi.org/10.1145/3293882.3338982
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                Degradation of software performance can become costly for companies and developers,
                  yet it is hardly assessed continuously. A strategy that would allow continuous performance
                  assessment of software libraries is software microbenchmarking, which faces ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  On domain knowledge and novelty to improve program synthesis performance with grammatical
                     evolution
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  • Erik Hemberg, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    •

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Programmers solve coding problems with the support of both programming and problem
                  specific knowledge. They integrate this domain knowledge to reason by computational
                  abstraction. Correct and readable code arises from sound abstractions and problem
                  ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Exposing hidden performance opportunities in high performance GPU applications
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    • Benjamin Welton, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    • Barton P. Miller
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      • 
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    CCGrid '18: Proceedings of the 18th IEEE/ACM International Symposium on Cluster, Cloud and Grid
                     ComputingMay 2018, pp 301–310https://doi.org/10.1109/CCGRID.2018.00045

                  have the potential to increase the performance of applications. Effectively exploiting
                  the parallelism provided by many-core accelerators requires developers to ...

                  by integration in an abstract SystemC model. Compared to existing simulation-based
                  approaches, we present a hybrid method that resolves performance issues by combining

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            User-friendly approach for handling performance parameters during predictive software
                     performance engineering
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            • Rasha Tawhid,

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            A Software Product Line (SPL) is a set of similar software systems that share a common
                  set of features. Instead of building each product from scratch, SPL development takes
                  advantage of the reusability of the core assets shared among the SPL members. In ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              Synthesizing programs that expose performance bottlenecks
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              • Luca Della Toffola, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              • Michael Pradel, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                •

Gross
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                • 
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              CGO 2018: Proceedings of the 2018 International Symposium on Code Generation and OptimizationFebruary 2018, pp 314–326https://doi.org/10.1145/3168830
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              Software often suffers from performance bottlenecks, e.g., because some code has a
                  higher computational complexity than expected or because a code change introduces
                  a performance regression. Finding such bottlenecks is challenging for developers and
                  for ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                Contention-aware application performance prediction for disaggregated memory systems
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                • Felippe Vieira Zacarias, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                • Rajiv Nishtala,

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                CF '20: Proceedings of the 17th ACM International Conference on Computing FrontiersMay 2020, pp 49–59https://doi.org/10.1145/3387902.3392625
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                Disaggregated memory has recently been proposed as a way to allow flexible and fine-grained
                  allocation of memory capacity to compute jobs. This paper makes an important step
                  towards effective resource allocation on disaggregated memory systems. ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Adaptive Performance Optimization under Power Constraint in Multi-thread Applications
                     with Diverse Scalability
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  • Stefano Conoci, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    •

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  ICPE '18: Proceedings of the 2018 ACM/SPEC International Conference on Performance EngineeringMarch 2018, pp 16–27https://doi.org/10.1145/3184407.3184419
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Energy consumption has become a core concern in computing systems. In this context,
                  power capping is an approach that aims at ensuring that the power consumption of a
                  system does not overcome a predefined threshold. Although various power capping ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    High-performance software rasterization on GPUs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    • Samuli Laine, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    • Tero Karras
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      • 
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    HPG '11: Proceedings of the ACM SIGGRAPH Symposium on High Performance GraphicsAugust 2011, pp 79–88https://doi.org/10.1145/2018323.2018337
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    In this paper, we implement an efficient, completely software-based graphics pipeline
                  on a GPU. Unlike previous approaches, we obey ordering constraints imposed by current
                  graphics APIs, guarantee hole-free rasterization, and support multisample ...

                  as high as 200%. We design and evaluate a new machine learning model that ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            Binary analysis for measurement and attribution of program performance

Tallent,

                  problems cannot be identified from costs attributed to routines in isolation; understanding
                  code performance requires information about a routine's calling ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Automatically identifying critical input regions and code in applications
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      • Michael Carbin, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      • Martin C. Rinard
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        • 
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      ISSTA '10: Proceedings of the 19th international symposium on Software testing and analysisJuly 2010, pp 37–48https://doi.org/10.1145/1831708.1831713
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Applications that process complex inputs often react in different ways to changes
                  in different regions of the input. Small changes to forgiving regions induce correspondingly
                  small changes in the behavior and output. Small changes to critical regions, ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      • 
                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          
                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        • 45

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              Automated program repair (in short, APR) has been attracting much attention. A variety
                  of APR techniques have been proposed, and they have been evaluated with actual bugs
                  in open source software. Currently, the authors are trying to introduce APR ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                Can cross-company data improve performance in software effort estimation?
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                • Leandro L. Minku, 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  • 
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                • Xin Yao
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  • 
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                PROMISE '12: Proceedings of the 8th International Conference on Predictive Models in Software EngineeringSeptember 2012, pp 69–78https://doi.org/10.1145/2365324.2365334
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                Background: There has been a long debate in the software engineering literature concerning how
                  useful cross-company (CC) data are for software effort estimation (SEE) in comparison
                  to within-company (WC) data. Studies indicate that models trained on CC ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Incorporating Software Performance Engineering Methods and Practices into the Software
                     Development Life Cycle
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  • André B. Bondi
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    • 
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  ICPE '16: Proceedings of the 7th ACM/SPEC on International Conference on Performance EngineeringMarch 2016, pp 327–330https://doi.org/10.1145/2851553.2858668
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
               		
               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  In many software development projects, attention is only paid to performance concerns
                  after functional testing, when it usually too late to remedy disabling performance
                  problems. Early attention to performance concerns and early planning of performance
                  ...

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            Identifying and (automatically) remedying performance problems in CPU/GPU applications

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              •

Miller

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            ICS '20: Proceedings of the 34th ACM International Conference on SupercomputingJune 2020, Article No.: 27, pp 1–13https://doi.org/10.1145/3392717.3392759

                  Effective exploitation of the additional parallelism offered by GPUs is fraught with
                  challenges.
